HEADWORD: Rectum
<hw>Rec"tum</hw> <pr>(-t?m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. (sc.
<ets>intestinum</ets>), fr. L. <ets>rectus</ets> straight. See
<er>Right</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The terminal part of the
large intestine; -- so named because supposed by the old anatomists to
be straight. See <xex>Illust.</xex> under <er>Digestive</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rectus</ent>⟦br⟧
